        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 7:56PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 756 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Eastwood, or 9 miles northeast of Bossier City, moving northwest at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shreveport, Bossier City, Haughton, Blanchard, Benton, Eastwood,
Alden Bridge, Ferguson, Princeton, Fillmore, Linton, Bodcau,
Bellevue, and Red Chute.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
